commentPostTextItems.html: Well played and congratulations to Australia for another comfortable win - on Australia Day. Well Pakistan will know that when it comes to pure talent, they were not far off. Australia were just led by a better captain, were much more alert with the running between the wickets and in the field, and won the big moments. That's the story of Pakistan's whole tour really. Thanks for joining us, okay bye

dismissalText.commentary: Kamran Akmal lbw b Harris 1 (2b 0x4 0x6 8m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: given! Akmal moves across to work it to the leg, misses it completely, Harris goes for the shout right away. Asoka de Silva upholds it. dismissalText.commentary: Salman Butt lbw b McKay 34 (39b 5x4 0x6 45m) SR: 87.17

dismissalComment.html: Asoka has struck again, no movement, going with angle, headed towards middle stump, and it had to be pitched outside leg. Asoka de Silva doesn't think so, and raises his finger. It's pitched way outside leg. What's more? It's going over the stumps. Salman Butt is furious as he walks off. No show of dissent at the wicket, though
